Run the HTTP API server for run execution

Usage: sprocket dev server start [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --host <HOST>
          Host to bind to

      --port <PORT>
          Port to bind to

      --database-url <DATABASE_URL>
          Database URL

  -o, --output-dir <OUTPUT_DIR>
          The output directory (default: `./out`)

      --allowed-file-paths <ALLOWED_FILE_PATHS>
          Allowed file paths for file-based workflows

      --allowed-urls <ALLOWED_URLS>
          Allowed URL prefixes for URL-based workflows

      --allowed-origins <ALLOWED_ORIGINS>
          Allowed CORS origins

  -m, --report-mode <MODE>
          The report mode for any emitted diagnostics

          Possible values:
          - full:     Prints diagnostics as multiple lines
          - one-line: Prints diagnostics as one line

  -v, --verbose...
          Increase logging verbosity

  -q, --quiet...
          Decrease logging verbosity

      --color <COLOR>
          Controls output colorization

          Possible values:
          - auto:   Automatically colorize output depending on output device
          - always: Always colorize output
          - never:  Never colorize output
          
          [default: auto]

  -c, --config <CONFIG>
          Path to the configuration file

  -s, --skip-config-search
          Skip searching for and loading configuration files.
          
          Only a configuration file specified as a command line argument will be used.

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version
